Cell["\<\
As this problem is very similar to the above problem, so is our solution. An \
additional for loop is added to bring the new sixTrack variable to the \
correct iteration. A new test has been added to the outermost While loop, \
accounting for the addition of the third variable, which needs to equal the \
other two. Additionally, inside of this While loop, 2 an additional If \
statements, containing while loops, are used to bring the value of the new \
sixTrack variable to be greater than or equal to the value of the other \
variables. When all of the variables are equivalent, the outermost While loop \
terminates. The x, y, and z values, along with the common number, are then \
printed using a Print statement.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.757815335811438*^9, 
  3.7578153433297477`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"73a97bea-2a2f-40ed-bedf-\
9e0e837c8d88"],

